---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';

const title = 'Privacy Policy | The Rooiberg Wander';
const description =
  'How The Rooiberg Wander (Franili Investments (Pty) Ltd) collects, uses and protects your personal information under POPIA.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} path="/privacy">
  <Section bg="cream" labelledby="privacy-heading">
    <div class="max-w-3xl privacy-body">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1 id="privacy-heading" class="font-display text-4xl text-earth sm:text-5xl">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="meta">Franili Investments (Pty) Ltd &middot; Last updated: July 2026</p>

      <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        The Rooiberg Wander is a division of <strong>Franili Investments (Pty) Ltd</strong>,
        a private company registered in South Africa (Reg.&nbsp;No.&nbsp;2021/392915/07,
        VAT&nbsp;Reg.&nbsp;No.&nbsp;4440301614) (&ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;us&rdquo;,
        &ldquo;our&rdquo;). We are the <strong>Responsible Party</strong> as defined in the
        Protection of Personal Information Act, 4 of 2013 (<strong>POPIA</strong>).
      </p>
      <p>
        Contact us at <a href="mailto:hanlie@rooibergwander.co.za">hanlie@rooibergwander.co.za</a>
        for any privacy-related query.
      </p>

      <h2>2. What personal information we collect</h2>
      <p>We collect only what is necessary to take and fulfil your booking.</p>
      <p><strong>At booking:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Full name, email address and mobile phone number of the lead guest</li>
        <li>Group size and residency status (local or international &mdash; affects pricing)</li>
        <li>Preferred trail start date</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>After booking (pre-trip form):</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Full names of all guests in your group</li>
        <li>Mobile number for guides on trail</li>
        <li>Vehicle make, model and registration (for secure parking at Rotavi Lodge)</li>
        <li>Estimated arrival time on Day 1</li>
        <li>Any relevant medical conditions, injuries, allergies or fitness limitations</li>
        <li>Special requests</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Payments:</strong></p>
      <p>
        We do not collect or store your card details. Payments are processed securely by
        <strong>Paystack</strong> (Paystack Commerce Limited, a Stripe company). Paystack handles
        all card data under their own PCI DSS compliance programme. We receive only a transaction
        reference and confirmation of payment.
      </p>
      <p><strong>Enquiries:</strong></p>
      <p>
        If you submit an enquiry through our website, we collect your name, email address and the
        content of your message.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Why we collect it (purpose and lawful basis)</h2>
      <p>We collect and use your personal information to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Process, confirm and administer your trail booking</li>
        <li>
          Communicate with you about your booking &mdash; confirmation, pre-trip reminders, payment
          links, and tax invoices
        </li>
        <li>
          Prepare for your trail experience: guest manifest, medical considerations, vehicle parking,
          and guide briefings
        </li>
        <li>Comply with our legal and regulatory obligations as a reserve access provider</li>
        <li>Respond to enquiries</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The primary lawful basis for processing is <strong>performance of a contract</strong>
        &mdash; we need this information to fulfil your booking. Where applicable, we also rely on
        our <strong>legitimate interests</strong> (e.g. fraud prevention, record-keeping) and
        <strong>legal obligation</strong>.
      </p>

      <h2>4. How long we keep it</h2>
      <p>
        We retain booking and pre-trip information for <strong>five years</strong> from your trail
        date, in line with our financial and VAT record-keeping obligations under South African
        law. Enquiries that do not result in a booking are retained for <strong>12 months</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>After these periods, personal information is securely deleted or anonymised.</p>

      <h2>5. Who we share it with</h2>
      <p>
        We share your information only with trusted service providers (operators/processors)
        necessary to fulfil your booking. We do not sell your personal information or share it with
        any third party for marketing purposes.
      </p>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Service provider</th>
              <th>Purpose</th>
              <th>Location</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Supabase Inc.</strong></td>
              <td>Database &mdash; booking and pre-trip records</td>
              <td>USA (AWS)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Paystack</strong> (Stripe)</td>
              <td>Payment processing</td>
              <td>Nigeria / USA</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Resend Inc.</strong></td>
              <td>Transactional email delivery</td>
              <td>USA</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Vercel Inc.</strong></td>
              <td>Website hosting and server functions</td>
              <td>USA</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p>
        These providers are bound by their own privacy policies and, where applicable, data
        processing agreements.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Cross-border transfers</h2>
      <p>
        Some of our service providers store and process personal data outside South Africa. Where
        this occurs, we use providers that maintain appropriate safeguards &mdash; including
        standard contractual clauses or comparable frameworks &mdash; as contemplated by section&nbsp;72
        of POPIA. By using our website and making a booking, you acknowledge that your information
        may be transferred to these countries.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Security</h2>
      <p>
        We implement appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect your personal
        information, including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Encrypted connections (HTTPS) on all pages</li>
        <li>Access controls limiting who can view personal data</li>
        <li>Row-level security on our database (records are not publicly readable)</li>
        <li>No storage of card details on our servers</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        No method of internet transmission is completely secure. If you believe your information has
        been compromised, please contact us immediately.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
      <p>Under POPIA, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong> &mdash; request a copy of the personal information we hold about you</li>
        <li><strong>Correction</strong> &mdash; request that inaccurate information be corrected</li>
        <li>
          <strong>Deletion</strong> &mdash; request that your information be deleted, subject to our
          legal retention obligations
        </li>
        <li><strong>Objection</strong> &mdash; object to specific processing of your information</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, email us at
        <a href="mailto:hanlie@rooibergwander.co.za">hanlie@rooibergwander.co.za</a>. We will
        respond within 30 days.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Cookies and analytics</h2>
      <p>
        Our website uses no advertising cookies and no cross-site tracking. If we use analytics,
        it is privacy-friendly, consent-aware and does not share your personal data with third
        parties for advertising purposes.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Complaints</h2>
      <p>
        If you are not satisfied with how we handle your personal information, you may lodge a
        complaint with the <strong>Information Regulator (South Africa)</strong>:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Website: <a href="https://www.inforegulator.org.za" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.inforegulator.org.za</a></li>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:POPIAComplaints@inforegulator.org.za">POPIAComplaints@inforegulator.org.za</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p>We would, however, appreciate the opportunity to address your concern directly first.</p>

      <h2>11. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. The date at the top of this page indicates
        when it was last revised. Continued use of our website following a material change
        constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .privacy-body {
    font-family: var(--font-body, system-ui, sans-serif);
    color: var(--color-charcoal, #2c2c2c);
  }
  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-ochre, #c19a6b);
  }
  .meta {
    margin: 0.75rem 0 2.5rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-charcoal, #2c2c2c) 55%, transparent);
  }
  .privacy-body h2 {
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0.75rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display, Georgia, serif);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-earth, #3d2b1f);
    line-height: 1.25;
  }
  .privacy-body p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
  .privacy-body ul {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 1.25rem;
    padding: 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
  .privacy-body li {
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }
  .privacy-body a {
    color: var(--color-green, #4a5d23);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .privacy-body a:hover {
    color: var(--color-earth, #3d2b1f);
  }
  .table-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.25rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-hairline, rgba(61,43,31,.10));
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
  }
  .table-wrap table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .table-wrap th {
    padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-charcoal, #2c2c2c) 55%, transparent);
    text-align: left;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-earth, #3d2b1f) 4%, transparent);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-hairline, rgba(61,43,31,.10));
  }
  .table-wrap td {
    padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-hairline, rgba(61,43,31,.10));
    color: var(--color-charcoal, #2c2c2c);
  }
  .table-wrap tr:last-child td {
    border-bottom: none;
  }
</style>
